The paper focuses on natural human-computer interaction and audio-visual human behavior sensing systems, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for automatic facial action unit detection and sentiment analysis, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of cultural studies in human behavior analysis, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
